{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:job.26",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 26,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 26",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 26 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:job.26.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:1",
      "text": "Then Job answered, and said:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.26.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:2",
      "text": "Whose helper art thou? is it of him that is weak? and dost thou hold up the arm of him that has no strength?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.26.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:3",
      "text": "To whom hast thou given counsel? perhaps to him that hath no wisdom, and thou hast shewn thy very great prudence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.26.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:4",
      "text": "Whom hast thou desired to teach? was it not him that made life?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.26.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:5",
      "text": "Behold the giants groan under the waters, and they that dwell with them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.26.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:6",
      "text": "Hell is naked before him, and there is no covering for destruction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.26.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:7",
      "text": "He stretched out the north over the empty space, and hangeth the earth upon nothing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.26.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:8",
      "text": "He bindeth up the waters in his clouds, so that they break not out and fall down together.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.26.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:9",
      "text": "He withholdeth the face of his throne, and spreadeth his cloud over it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.26.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:10",
      "text": "He hath set bounds about the waters, till light and darkness come to an end.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.26.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:11",
      "text": "The pillars of heaven tremble, and dread at his beck.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.26.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:12",
      "text": "By his power the seas are suddenly gathered together, and his wisdom has struck the proud one.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.26.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:13",
      "text": "His spirit hath adorned the heavens, and his obstetric hand brought forth the winding serpent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.26.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:14",
      "text": "Lo, these things are said in part of his ways: and seeing we have heard scarce a little drop of his word, who shall be able to behold the thunder of his greatness?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
